diff --git a/skills/review-request/SKILL.md b/skills/review-request/SKILL.md
index f69575a22..ac38a1373 100644
--- a/skills/review-request/SKILL.md
+++ b/skills/review-request/SKILL.md
@@ -139,7 +139,7 @@ ## Customer-repo done-definition (Non-Negotiable)
 
 The agent's done-definition depends on who owns the repo:
 
-- **Customer / colleague-facing repos** (an overlay running `autonomy notify`): the agent's job is DONE when the **MR is mergeable + review-requestable**. The agent must NOT merge (that needs colleague approval), and — because the `notify` tier resolves `review_request_post_disabled = true` — must NOT request review itself. Agent-driven review-request is **blocked by the tier** on such an overlay: do NOT ask the user to approve a review-request post and do NOT auto-post one. The `t3 <overlay> review-request post` path refuses (the `#960` chokepoint blocks) because `resolve_on_behalf_verdict("review_request_post")` BLOCKs regardless of `on_behalf_post_mode` (including the `immediate` value the autonomy collapse forces). Stop at mergeable; report the PR link and that it is ready for the user to request review.
+- **Customer / colleague-facing repos** (an overlay running `autonomy notify`): the agent's job is DONE when the **MR is mergeable + review-requestable**. The agent must NOT merge (that needs colleague approval), and — because the `notify` tier resolves `review_request_post_disabled = true` — must NOT request review itself. Agent-driven review-request is **blocked by the tier** on such an overlay: do NOT ask the user to approve a review-request post and do NOT auto-post one. The `t3 <overlay> review-request post` path refuses (the `#960` chokepoint blocks) because `resolve_on_behalf_verdict("review_request_post")` BLOCKs regardless of `on_behalf_post_mode` (including the `immediate` value the autonomy collapse forces). Stop at mergeable; report the PR link and that it is ready for the user to request review. To confirm read-only that the MR is mergeable + review-requestable, run `t3 <overlay> review-request discover` (or `t3 <overlay> review-request check --mr-url <url>` for a single MR) — it validates CI + metadata and posts nothing.
 - **Tooling repos** (`souliane/teatree` and the user's solo-owned tooling overlay repos, running `autonomy full`): review-request PROCEEDs and the agent DOES merge its own green, cold-review-cleared work via the keystone.
 
 The enforcement is driven off the per-overlay `autonomy` TIER, not a side flag: the `notify` tier resolves `review_request_post_disabled = true`, which forces the review-request BLOCK even when the collapse has set `on_behalf_post_mode = immediate`; the `full` tier resolves it `false` (review-request proceeds). Run a customer overlay on `t3 <overlay> autonomy set notify --overlay <name>`; run a solo tooling overlay on `autonomy full`. The Option-A per-overlay escape stays available: `t3 <overlay> config_setting set review_request_post_disabled <true|false> --overlay <name>` explicitly pins the field and wins over the tier (a `full` overlay can pin `true` to suppress auto-request; a `notify` overlay can pin `false` to opt back in). It is orthogonal to `require_human_approval_to_merge` (which gates merge, not the review-request post).
